WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:04.000
[pages riffling]

00:07.875 --> 00:11.000
♪ dramatic theme playing ♪

00:11.000 --> 00:14.000
♪

00:17.000 --> 00:19.583
[muffled shouting]
[raspy breathing]

00:19.583 --> 00:21.542
[muffled shouting continues]

00:24.125 --> 00:25.708
[monitor beeping]

00:25.708 --> 00:26.958
‐ Where are the rest?

00:26.958 --> 00:29.958
‐ There was no one else, sir.
He was the only one who survived.

00:29.958 --> 00:32.792
‐ There were two dozen
elite soldiers on that mountain!

00:32.792 --> 00:35.417
This wounded lump of shit
is all that's left?

00:35.417 --> 00:37.292
[groaning]

00:38.250 --> 00:41.042
‐ Mon‐key!

00:41.708 --> 00:43.167
[beeping quickens]

00:43.167 --> 00:45.417
[flatline]

00:45.417 --> 00:46.958
‐ What the hell does that mean?

00:46.958 --> 00:49.375
MEDIC: I don't know.
He's been saying it since we found him.

00:49.375 --> 00:51.542
‐ We think that's who attacked him.
A monkey.

00:51.542 --> 00:53.417
‐ Monkeys don't shoot guns!

00:53.417 --> 00:55.375
Monkeys don't even use tools!

00:55.375 --> 00:56.833
‐ Actually, sir, I saw a documentary‐‐

00:56.833 --> 01:00.375
‐ Shut up! Monkey is
a codename, you idiot!

01:02.625 --> 01:04.167
Find this Monkey.

01:04.167 --> 01:06.042
And when you do,

01:06.042 --> 01:09.333
I want him erased
from the face of the goddamn Earth!

01:09.333 --> 01:10.458
‐ Yes, sir!

01:10.458 --> 01:12.833
♪ dramatic theme continues ♪

01:12.833 --> 01:15.333
♪

01:24.792 --> 01:26.042
BRYCE:
I know, it's weird, right?

01:26.042 --> 01:28.292
So I'm heading towards this light,
and I'm psyched for my life

01:28.292 --> 01:30.208
to flash before my eyes because,

01:30.208 --> 01:33.000
well, there's a lot of baller shit
in there that I'd love to see, you know.

01:33.000 --> 01:36.375
Especially the adult content. And some
of the bloopers, if I'm being honest.

01:36.375 --> 01:38.417
But I didn't see any of that. Nothing. No.

01:38.417 --> 01:40.083
All I saw was you.
[Monkey grunts]

01:40.083 --> 01:43.042
Which is ironic because,
well, I just met you

01:43.042 --> 01:44.958
and I'm pretty sure you hate my guts.

01:44.958 --> 01:47.208
But hey, man, we are linked. You know?

01:47.208 --> 01:48.792
Linked, but in two different realms.

01:48.792 --> 01:51.208
You know what? I'm like Swayze
and you're Demi Moore.

01:52.292 --> 01:53.917
Hello. Ghost?

01:53.917 --> 01:55.500
Okay, not a big rom‐com guy, all right.

01:55.500 --> 01:57.667
Oh, oh, I know,
I'm Slimer, and you're Venkman.

01:58.167 --> 01:59.750
Nothing, huh? Seriously? Wow.

01:59.750 --> 02:02.292
Uh, I'm Beetlejuice
and you're Winona Ryder?

02:02.292 --> 02:04.667
Uh, I'm the rotting chick in the bathtub
and you're Jack Nicholson!

02:05.125 --> 02:07.667
[screeches]
I mean, beats me, man, you know,

02:07.667 --> 02:09.792
some ghosts haunt a place.
Some haunt people.

02:09.792 --> 02:11.833
Maybe I'm just forced
to haunt a dumb animal.

02:11.833 --> 02:12.958
[whooshing]

02:12.958 --> 02:14.792
[Monkey screeches]

02:14.792 --> 02:17.875
I'm just trying to wrap my head around
what the heck's going on with me.

02:17.875 --> 02:19.583
Like, is this Purgatory?

02:19.583 --> 02:22.792
Sitting on top of a train with a monkey
that yells at you the whole time?

02:22.792 --> 02:23.667
[screeches]

02:23.667 --> 02:26.542
That's what I'm trying
to tell you: I can't.

02:28.917 --> 02:30.542
See? This is what I'm talking about.

02:30.542 --> 02:31.875
It's like a ghost‐leash.

02:33.458 --> 02:36.833
Regarding you and me, though,
I know I could be very helpful to you.

02:36.833 --> 02:38.250
You know, I know where all
the bodies are buried,

02:38.250 --> 02:41.417
and you, well, um,
I mean, you can learn, right?

02:41.417 --> 02:43.375
[growls]
Okay, so what's your plan?

02:43.792 --> 02:45.333
You just gonna kill everyone you meet?

02:46.542 --> 02:47.792
[huffing]

02:47.792 --> 02:48.583
Okay!

02:48.917 --> 02:50.333
Yeah, no, suit yourself.

02:50.875 --> 02:54.333
Oh, dude, you are gonna love Tokyo.

02:55.417 --> 02:58.500
♪

02:59.417 --> 03:00.667
[horn honks]

03:00.667 --> 03:01.583
[tires squealing]
[siren wailing]

03:01.583 --> 03:03.042
[camera shutter clicks]

03:04.208 --> 03:05.833
[hoots]

03:08.417 --> 03:09.417
[horn honks]

03:09.417 --> 03:10.667
[horn blares]

03:14.083 --> 03:16.208
[indiscernible conversations]

03:28.625 --> 03:30.208
[whimpers]

03:32.333 --> 03:34.958
Ho ho ho. Hey,
I told you you'd love it here!

03:34.958 --> 03:36.208
[grumbles]

03:36.208 --> 03:37.375
Come on, follow me.

03:37.375 --> 03:40.000
If you're into scummy dark places,
I got the perfect spot for you.

03:46.542 --> 03:48.625
[crowd screaming]

03:48.625 --> 03:50.792
ITO:
No! No, no. Wait, Hiroshi!

03:50.792 --> 03:52.500
[gunshots]

03:53.208 --> 03:54.417
Hiroshi...

03:55.625 --> 03:58.375
POLICE CAPTAIN: [muffled] Clock in
over there if you want to get paid.

03:58.375 --> 04:00.708
That's the vending machine.
Never works.

04:00.708 --> 04:04.750
[chuckles]
And here is the famous Lieutenant Ito.

04:04.750 --> 04:06.583
The pride of the department.

04:06.583 --> 04:08.083
‐ Hmm.
POLICE CAPTAIN: Lieutenant,

04:08.083 --> 04:10.542
I'd like to introduce you
to your new partner,

04:10.542 --> 04:12.625
Haruka.
‐ Hi. Hello.

04:12.625 --> 04:14.708
POLICE CAPTAIN:
She comes very highly recommended.

04:15.208 --> 04:17.833
I trust you'll make her feel
right at home.

04:17.833 --> 04:19.208
‐ I'm off duty.

04:19.750 --> 04:21.583
Unless you want to watch me eat.

04:21.583 --> 04:22.875
‐ Oh.

04:22.875 --> 04:24.125
‐ Good luck.

04:24.875 --> 04:27.208
HARUKA: I am very honored
to be working with you, Ito‐san.

04:27.208 --> 04:28.542
‐ You talk funny,

04:28.542 --> 04:30.792
where are you from?
‐ Oh, Hokkaido.

04:30.792 --> 04:32.833
Actually from an island called Rishiri.

04:32.833 --> 04:35.667
‐ Never heard of it.
‐ Not a lot of people know about it.

04:35.667 --> 04:37.833
You can see Russia
from our police station.

04:37.833 --> 04:40.542
I was the number one
police officer in my island.

04:40.542 --> 04:42.042
‐ How many officers in total?

04:42.708 --> 04:44.792
‐ Two. Including me.
‐ Hmm.

04:46.333 --> 04:49.458
Orimasta. I'll take a double brandy
and a fish cake.

04:49.458 --> 04:52.292
‐ Just water.
‐ Okay, confession time.

04:52.292 --> 04:53.875
What did they tell you about me?

04:53.875 --> 04:56.375
‐ That you're a 20‐year
veteran of the force

04:56.375 --> 04:58.583
and that I should listen
and learn from you.

04:58.583 --> 05:00.958
‐ Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah,
and then there was a "but."

05:00.958 --> 05:02.375
What came after the "but"?

05:02.375 --> 05:03.833
‐ You could have made captain,

05:03.833 --> 05:07.625
but you took a bribe
and it damaged your career.

05:07.625 --> 05:08.750
That you don't follow protocol

05:08.750 --> 05:11.917
and... that you may have
a slight drinking problem.

05:11.917 --> 05:13.542
‐ Yep, that's pretty accurate.

05:13.542 --> 05:15.875
‐ And you're obsessed with trying
to find your partner's killer.

05:15.875 --> 05:17.375
‐ There's no try.

05:17.375 --> 05:19.708
I am going to find the person responsible.

05:19.708 --> 05:21.917
And when I do, I promise you,

05:21.917 --> 05:23.500
I'm not going to arrest them.

05:24.042 --> 05:25.917
‐ What? You want me to arrest them?

05:25.917 --> 05:28.333
‐ No, I'm going to kill them.

05:28.958 --> 05:29.958
‐ Oh.

05:30.917 --> 05:31.875
Got it.

05:35.500 --> 05:38.208
BRYCE: Okay, so this lady was
my only real point of contact.

05:38.208 --> 05:40.000
I say we just play it
old school, you know.

05:40.000 --> 05:42.708
Walk in there, hold a gun to her face,
demand the info.

05:42.708 --> 05:45.917
And remember, the whole goal
is maximum intimidation,

05:45.917 --> 05:47.625
so act like you're a little nuts.

05:47.625 --> 05:49.417
Which, you know, shouldn't be
a problem for you.

05:49.417 --> 05:50.375
[hoots]

05:50.375 --> 05:52.917
Of course it's safe.
No, she's an old‐ass lady.

05:55.667 --> 05:58.333
♪

05:59.250 --> 06:01.208
[bubbling]
[whimpers]

06:03.000 --> 06:04.125
BRYCE:
Hey, dude.

06:04.125 --> 06:06.708
They're already sashimi. Let's go.

06:08.083 --> 06:10.208
Ah. Maybe it's her night off.

06:10.792 --> 06:12.042
Or maybe she's dead.

06:12.667 --> 06:15.583
This lady had, like, full‐blown
Tuberculosis the last time I saw her.

06:15.583 --> 06:17.333
Just coughing every‐‐
Oh, my God.

06:17.333 --> 06:18.375
Will you look at this?

06:18.375 --> 06:20.917
She's running, like,
15 different Keno games at once.

06:20.917 --> 06:23.917
This chick's like
the Bobby Fischer of Keno.

06:23.917 --> 06:26.542
And evidently supplies
half the guns in Japan.

06:28.417 --> 06:29.417
Oh, shit.

06:30.417 --> 06:31.417
[gas hisses]

06:31.417 --> 06:33.125
[Monkey hoots]
BRYCE: Goddammit!

06:33.750 --> 06:35.333
[coughs]

06:36.292 --> 06:39.292
[menacing laughter]

06:43.583 --> 06:45.000
[hoots]

06:49.792 --> 06:51.250
‐ Hey, there he is!

06:51.250 --> 06:53.000
Okay, clearly I misjudged this chick.

06:53.000 --> 06:54.958
[hooting, screeching]

06:54.958 --> 06:58.208
Okay, look, I understand you're having
a very hard time right now.

06:58.208 --> 07:00.583
Can you, uh, maybe work
on some hand signals, you know.

07:00.583 --> 07:03.375
Like sign language? 'Cause the screeching
here is super annoying.

07:03.375 --> 07:04.250
[screeching]

07:05.583 --> 07:09.625
Okay, dude, there's a piece of metal,
like a hook or something for another belt.

07:09.625 --> 07:11.542
If you reach under it,
you might be able to bend it.

07:12.750 --> 07:15.208
Will you look at that!
Opposable thumbs for the win!

07:16.083 --> 07:19.667
Woo! There you go! Jane Goodall would
have shit her khakis if she saw that!

07:19.667 --> 07:20.667
Whoo‐hoo!

07:25.833 --> 07:26.667
[whooshes]

07:27.458 --> 07:28.958
[menacing laughter]

07:29.833 --> 07:32.125
‐ Oh, you're dead now, rat!

07:32.125 --> 07:33.958
[Monkey screeches]
BRYCE: Run!

07:36.375 --> 07:38.625
[laughter continues]

07:38.625 --> 07:39.708
[coughing]

07:39.708 --> 07:41.708
‐ Here, monkey, monkey, monkey.

07:41.708 --> 07:44.667
You want to play a little hide and seek?

07:44.667 --> 07:47.292
‐ Keep going, buddy! Keep going!
You got it. Don't look back!

07:47.292 --> 07:50.167
[screeches]
Holy shit! This lady is mean!

07:50.167 --> 07:52.750
‐ There's nowhere to run, little monkey.

07:52.750 --> 07:55.250
‐ I'm gonna set a pick on her ass!
Keep going, I got ya!

07:55.833 --> 07:57.208
Oh, that's right, I'm a ghost.

07:58.292 --> 07:59.875
[hooting]

08:01.458 --> 08:02.375
[groans]

08:03.042 --> 08:03.792
[bones crunching]

08:03.792 --> 08:06.875
[screaming]

08:11.000 --> 08:13.417
‐ I don't need two arms to kill you!

08:13.792 --> 08:15.667
BRYCE: Oh, my God,
she's just gonna play through it.

08:15.667 --> 08:17.292
This woman's nuts!

08:17.292 --> 08:19.667
‐ You're gonna die!

08:19.667 --> 08:21.583
[laughing]

08:23.417 --> 08:25.292
[screaming]

08:25.292 --> 08:26.583
BRYCE: Hey, hey!

08:27.375 --> 08:30.000
Wow!
OLD WOMAN: You dickhead!

08:31.042 --> 08:32.250
[grunts]

08:32.250 --> 08:33.625
No!

08:33.625 --> 08:34.958
Help me!

08:34.958 --> 08:37.208
Help me!
‐ All right, lady, who do you work for?

08:37.208 --> 08:39.875
Who do you work for?
Oh, shit. She can't hear me.

08:39.875 --> 08:41.583
Hey! Ask her who she works for!

08:41.583 --> 08:42.875
[hooting]

08:42.875 --> 08:44.667
‐ Pull the plug!

08:44.667 --> 08:46.833
‐ Do you really not know
any sign language?

08:46.833 --> 08:48.583
[screeching]

08:48.583 --> 08:50.708
‐ You cock‐sucker!

08:54.333 --> 08:57.250
BRYCE:
Ewwww‐whew‐hew‐hew.

08:58.417 --> 09:00.250
Okay. Okay. Good effort.

09:01.250 --> 09:03.125
All right, so which half
do you want to interrogate?

09:03.125 --> 09:04.500
[grunting]

09:05.500 --> 09:07.875
Hey! Hey!

09:07.875 --> 09:09.208
Aren't you forgetting something?

09:11.208 --> 09:12.417
[hooting]

09:12.417 --> 09:15.333
It's money. You know, cash.
Moolah. Ducats.

09:15.917 --> 09:16.917
How do I explain this?

09:16.917 --> 09:20.083
Okay, look, you know how sometimes
another monkey has something you want,

09:20.083 --> 09:23.125
like, I don't know, a banana
or a bunch of cocaine?

09:23.125 --> 09:24.833
Well, this is how you get them
to give you that.

09:24.833 --> 09:25.542
[grunts]

09:26.458 --> 09:27.792
[zips up]

09:34.042 --> 09:36.417
[siren wailing]

09:38.000 --> 09:40.458
[man grunting]

09:40.458 --> 09:43.792
♪

09:46.750 --> 09:49.542
Ugh, will you stop
beating yourself up.

09:49.542 --> 09:52.417
I mean, you heard that lady's cough.
She was going to die anyway.

09:52.417 --> 09:54.583
She probably had, like,
an hour to live. Tops.

09:54.583 --> 09:55.375
[hooting]

09:55.375 --> 09:57.000
No, no, it's not blood money.

09:57.000 --> 09:59.625
I mean, yes.
No, it's literally splattered with blood,

09:59.625 --> 10:01.250
yeah, but you earned it, you know.

10:01.250 --> 10:04.167
And now we can use it to find
some place out of the way.

10:04.167 --> 10:05.667
Someplace like, um‐‐

10:06.375 --> 10:08.375
Yeah. Du‐du‐du‐du‐du. Hmm.

10:09.042 --> 10:10.208
This one has free wi‐fi.

10:12.083 --> 10:15.417
♪ instrumental music
playing on speakers ♪

10:15.417 --> 10:17.542
♪

10:17.542 --> 10:18.417
‐ Huh?

10:20.417 --> 10:24.667
♪

10:27.167 --> 10:30.042
♪ music continues ♪

10:36.292 --> 10:37.583
[clicking]

10:39.000 --> 10:41.792
‐ Well, okay. Oh, here we go.

10:43.792 --> 10:45.833
Oh, yup. Yup.

10:45.833 --> 10:47.333
This is a goddamn nightmare.

10:48.542 --> 10:50.458
[car alarms blaring]

10:52.625 --> 10:53.667
[sighs]

10:54.250 --> 10:55.542
Hey, can I get a little help here?

10:58.417 --> 10:59.708
Lame. Why don't you see
what else is on.

11:00.583 --> 11:02.000
Oh. Great.

11:02.000 --> 11:03.917
Hey, this means "thanks a lot."

11:03.917 --> 11:05.542
First sign‐language lesson for you.

11:05.542 --> 11:06.625
[grunts]

11:12.958 --> 11:15.125
Hey, I'd be careful
using that hot tub if I were you,

11:15.125 --> 11:17.667
or the next person you'll have
to hunt down is a dermatologist.

11:18.542 --> 11:20.083
[Monkey groans sadly]

11:20.083 --> 11:24.042
♪

11:31.750 --> 11:35.625
‐ Everyone is just devastated
by Ken's untimely passing,

11:35.625 --> 11:37.000
most of all me.

11:37.375 --> 11:40.542
I was looking forward
to beating him at the polls.

11:40.542 --> 11:43.250
This just feels like such a letdown.

11:43.250 --> 11:44.292
‐ I'm sure.

11:44.292 --> 11:47.958
‐ So I'm here to graciously say that
I'm going to stop running ads,

11:47.958 --> 11:49.458
cancel my rallies.

11:49.458 --> 11:51.875
You know, out of respect
for Ken's memory.

11:51.875 --> 11:55.833
Since it's pretty obvious... I've won.

11:56.875 --> 11:58.708
Better luck next time.

12:01.250 --> 12:03.208
‐ What a scumbag!

12:03.208 --> 12:06.125
He wasn't here to give his condolences,
he was here to gloat!

12:06.125 --> 12:08.833
Like the pig he is.
‐ Akiko, not now.

12:08.833 --> 12:11.333
‐ And look at us!
What a bunch of wimps.

12:11.333 --> 12:12.792
Why did we give up?

12:12.792 --> 12:15.292
We were only a few points behind
and gaining before‐‐

12:15.292 --> 12:17.750
‐ Before what? Ken got shot?

12:17.750 --> 12:19.875
Before our candidate got killed?

12:19.875 --> 12:21.583
I've got news for you:

12:21.583 --> 12:24.875
you can't have a campaign
without a candidate.

12:24.875 --> 12:27.792
‐ We do have a candidate.
You!

12:27.792 --> 12:29.083
‐ What are you talking about?

12:29.083 --> 12:30.875
‐ You know Ken's whole strategy.

12:30.875 --> 12:33.458
You've been helping him get elected
his entire career.

12:33.458 --> 12:35.208
‐ I'm a total unknown.

12:35.208 --> 12:37.875
It's less than six weeks
before the election,

12:37.875 --> 12:39.958
and I'm not Ken.

12:39.958 --> 12:42.208
I can't speak like him.

12:42.208 --> 12:44.292
‐ Yes, you can. I could help you.

12:44.292 --> 12:45.583
There would be so much good will.

12:45.583 --> 12:47.750
The people are crying out
for someone to pick up the baton.

12:47.750 --> 12:49.708
It's waiting for you, uncle.

12:50.583 --> 12:52.208
It's what Ken would have wanted.

12:55.750 --> 12:57.583
[grunting]

12:57.583 --> 13:00.500
[hooting]

13:02.292 --> 13:04.458
[screeching]

13:09.417 --> 13:11.250
‐ Buddy, you up? Buddy?

13:11.708 --> 13:13.125
Hey!
[hoots]

13:13.125 --> 13:15.417
Oh, what a nightmare.
Apparently, I don't sleep.

13:15.417 --> 13:16.458
You know. Like, at all.

13:16.458 --> 13:18.875
Just thinking about shit, you know.
Waiting for you to get up.

13:18.875 --> 13:21.000
By the way, I don't know
if you've been told this before,

13:21.000 --> 13:22.083
but you talk in your sleep.

13:22.083 --> 13:24.000
Uh, screech. It's loud as shit, too.

13:24.333 --> 13:28.417
Scary. Hey, look, I don't mind being alone
with my thoughts, but only, like,

13:28.417 --> 13:31.750
for that couple of minutes on a plane
where you have to put your phone away.

13:31.750 --> 13:34.125
A whole night of that stuff. No, thanks.
[door opens]

13:36.042 --> 13:38.000
Dude, where you going?

13:38.708 --> 13:40.125
[indiscernible police radio chatter]
[siren wailing]

13:40.125 --> 13:41.292
[camera shutter clicks]

13:41.875 --> 13:44.208
‐ Back in my day,
a crime scene just meant a shooting.

13:46.417 --> 13:48.333
Huh. Strange.

13:48.333 --> 13:51.583
She chased whoever killed her
high up into that machine.

13:51.583 --> 13:54.750
‐ Must've been an excellent climber.
And small.

13:55.833 --> 13:57.583
Maybe a circus person?

13:57.583 --> 13:59.625
‐ Go and get the serial numbers
off those guns.

13:59.625 --> 14:03.167
I bet you'll find they have something
to do with the Takahara assassination.

14:04.000 --> 14:06.667
♪

14:09.833 --> 14:13.375
‐ Man, I don't think I've been sober
this long for, like, 20 years.

14:13.375 --> 14:14.917
This is a terrible idea, by the way.

14:14.917 --> 14:16.750
Only a complete idiot goes back
to the scene of the‐‐

14:16.750 --> 14:18.125
Oh, my God, who is this?

14:20.917 --> 14:25.167
Why is a General stopping by
to check out‐‐ Holy shit! 128th!

14:25.167 --> 14:28.292
Those are the dickheads
that met me at the airport.

14:29.083 --> 14:31.875
This must be the asshole
who ordered them to kill me.

14:31.875 --> 14:32.708
[growls]

14:32.708 --> 14:34.292
Right. Right‐right‐right. Sorry.

14:34.292 --> 14:37.042
And your whole monkey tribe. Or village.

14:37.042 --> 14:38.875
Or pod. Or whatever, you know‐‐

14:40.000 --> 14:43.083
♪ dramatic music playing ♪

14:43.083 --> 14:45.667
♪

14:45.667 --> 14:49.250
Woo! Yes, sir!
Brycie's still got it, baby!

14:49.250 --> 14:52.333
See, this is why you always return
to the scene of a crime.

14:53.750 --> 14:55.250
Come on, come on, come on,
let's go, you're losing him!

14:55.250 --> 14:57.083
[Monkey screeches]
Hey, pal,

14:57.083 --> 14:59.208
I'm working just as hard
as you are, okay.

14:59.208 --> 15:01.333
[chuckles] Woo!

15:06.375 --> 15:09.500
[wind gusting]

15:09.500 --> 15:12.667
♪ tense music playing ♪

15:12.667 --> 15:15.583
♪

15:16.667 --> 15:17.458
[door opens]

15:21.375 --> 15:22.583
‐ Off, monkey!

15:22.583 --> 15:23.917
[hoots]

15:26.125 --> 15:29.292
‐ Oh. Wait, hold up.
Uh‐uh. Time out.

15:29.292 --> 15:30.500
No, no, no, no, no.

15:30.500 --> 15:33.542
No way. Nope. I've never been
to the funeral of someone I've killed,

15:33.542 --> 15:34.958
and I'm not about to start now.

15:34.958 --> 15:36.833
It's like getting brunch
with a one‐night stand.

15:36.833 --> 15:39.542
Your time together is over. I don't need
to eat French Toast with you.

15:40.333 --> 15:41.958
Whoa, whoa, whoa! Whoa! Whoa!

15:41.958 --> 15:43.583
Wait a minute! Stop! Halt!

15:43.583 --> 15:45.875
Jesus, if you're so hell‐bent on going in,

15:45.875 --> 15:48.583
at least use the back door
like a professional.

15:52.250 --> 15:54.333
I gotta say, being dead sucks.

15:54.333 --> 15:57.042
But some shit?
Lot easier than when I was alive.

15:57.583 --> 15:59.042
Like this stuff.

15:59.042 --> 16:02.292
Whoa‐ho‐ho! You look like
you're rocking a butt‐hawk, dude.

16:02.292 --> 16:04.417
Not a good look.
We gotta get you a disguise.

16:04.417 --> 16:08.125
I can literally see your sphincter
clenching with effort right now.

16:08.125 --> 16:09.375
[hoots]

16:10.542 --> 16:13.042
♪ tense music playing ♪

16:13.042 --> 16:15.292
♪

16:15.292 --> 16:17.708
Okay, buddy, eyes on the prize.

16:17.708 --> 16:20.792
[sniffs]
This here is a real hornet's nest,

16:20.792 --> 16:22.583
so the quicker we can get in
and get out, the better.

16:22.583 --> 16:24.375
[stomach rumbles]
[groans]

16:24.375 --> 16:26.083
What‐‐ Oh! Or that...

16:27.208 --> 16:29.542
♪

16:30.167 --> 16:31.500
[laughter]

16:33.458 --> 16:34.292
[grunts]

16:35.583 --> 16:36.458
[laughter]

16:36.458 --> 16:38.958
‐ Pay up, bitches!
‐ Dammit!

16:42.833 --> 16:45.833
MRS. TAKAHARA: Because a coward took
my husband from us.

16:46.667 --> 16:48.542
A coward with a gun.

16:48.542 --> 16:51.375
Small minded and weak.

16:51.375 --> 16:54.250
Who felt that the only way
he could matter in this world

16:54.250 --> 16:57.958
was to take someone
who did matter from all of us.

16:57.958 --> 17:00.375
‐ Yeesh, that's a little harsh.

17:00.375 --> 17:04.042
‐ The world won't remember
this small inconsequential man,

17:04.875 --> 17:08.333
but they will remember my husband.

17:08.333 --> 17:09.583
[applause]

17:17.958 --> 17:20.000
[laughter]

17:21.917 --> 17:25.125
♪

17:27.458 --> 17:28.458
[squawks]

17:30.167 --> 17:31.500
‐ Monkey!
[hoots]

17:32.042 --> 17:33.875
Monkey, you're my friend!

17:35.500 --> 17:37.208
No, you're mine!

17:40.042 --> 17:42.458
KATO:
I was promised money.

17:42.458 --> 17:45.000
I was promised I'd be a hero!

17:45.000 --> 17:47.792
But now I lost two squads of men.

17:47.792 --> 17:51.375
I've got no money.
And people are dying everywhere!

17:52.458 --> 17:55.500
Please. I know
this is highly inappropriate

17:55.500 --> 17:57.667
for me to be speaking with you.

17:57.667 --> 18:01.208
I understand none of us are supposed
to know who was involved.

18:01.208 --> 18:04.125
But I'm facing real pressure to explain

18:04.125 --> 18:05.542
what happened up there.

18:05.542 --> 18:06.958
[man sighs]

18:06.958 --> 18:10.208
MAN:
It's a very fluid situation.

18:10.208 --> 18:12.042
But it's being contained.

18:12.042 --> 18:14.083
KATO:
The hell does that mean?

18:14.083 --> 18:15.792
Just tell me, am I next?

18:16.292 --> 18:18.667
Are you cleaning house?

18:18.667 --> 18:20.958
Am I getting thrown
under the goddamn bus?

18:24.000 --> 18:25.583
[grunts]

18:26.208 --> 18:30.833
MAN: I'm sorry. You must have me
confused with someone else.

18:31.208 --> 18:33.958
‐ Wait a minute, why am I hiding?
I'm invisible.

18:35.542 --> 18:37.167
What? What the hell?
What? No.

18:37.167 --> 18:39.083
No, no, no. No! No!

18:39.083 --> 18:40.250
Shit!

18:41.083 --> 18:43.250
Argh! Dammit!

18:43.250 --> 18:45.250
[Monkey screeching]
[kid yelling]

18:46.917 --> 18:48.583
[kid grunts]
‐ Hey!

18:49.250 --> 18:50.708
No, monkey. No!

18:50.708 --> 18:52.333
[whimpers, sighs]

18:53.750 --> 18:56.750
♪

19:05.083 --> 19:06.958
♪ Deerhoof's Believe E. S. P. playing ♪

19:06.958 --> 19:09.250
♪

19:13.208 --> 19:14.542
‐ ♪ Obsession ♪

19:15.500 --> 19:17.167
♪ You're reading my mind ♪

19:17.167 --> 19:19.375
♪ How sad ♪

19:19.375 --> 19:22.458
‐ There you are. Where‐‐ Holy shit.

19:22.458 --> 19:25.542
Wow, I never thought a six‐inch inseam
would turn me on.

19:25.542 --> 19:27.500
Seriously, you look like a badass.

19:27.500 --> 19:29.125
I mean, you could use
a good tailor though.

19:29.125 --> 19:30.333
And you're missing the tie.

19:31.125 --> 19:32.958
Dude, you have to wear the tie.

19:32.958 --> 19:35.333
The suit's too formal.
It just looks sloppy without it.

19:35.792 --> 19:37.125
Oh, oh, oh, I get it.

19:37.125 --> 19:38.750
You don't know how to tie a tie, do you?

19:39.417 --> 19:40.833
Don't worry, I'll teach you.

19:42.917 --> 19:44.667
‐ Cool!

19:44.667 --> 19:47.292
[applause]

19:54.333 --> 19:57.292
‐ Ken would have hated this.

19:58.250 --> 20:01.000
Because for Ken,
it wasn't about him.

20:01.792 --> 20:04.292
It was about the cause.

20:04.292 --> 20:06.750
It was about the fight for justice

20:06.750 --> 20:08.625
and equality.

20:08.625 --> 20:11.042
About rooting out the corruption

20:11.042 --> 20:13.625
that is a cancer of our country.

20:13.625 --> 20:17.750
This was the great unfinished business
of his life.

20:17.750 --> 20:21.208
And it's up to us to finish it.
[mouthing words]

20:21.208 --> 20:22.917
[applause]

20:22.917 --> 20:25.333
‐ Come on, we have to move together.
Follow the weird Bonsai shoes.

20:25.333 --> 20:26.458
[hoots]

20:26.458 --> 20:29.542
No, dumbass, if I could see his face,
I wouldn't need you.

20:29.542 --> 20:30.875
SHINJI:
...you and I.

20:30.875 --> 20:33.750
Let us pick up the baton

20:33.750 --> 20:35.708
that lies in the mud,

20:35.708 --> 20:37.750
bloodied and forgotten.

20:37.750 --> 20:40.167
Let us carry it on.

20:40.167 --> 20:43.000
To finish the race he started,

20:43.000 --> 20:45.292
and to win.

20:45.292 --> 20:48.542
[cheering and applause]
‐ Bravo.

20:50.917 --> 20:52.833
‐ That wasn't a eulogy,

20:52.833 --> 20:56.000
that was a goddamn campaign speech.

20:56.000 --> 20:57.208
Out of my way!

20:58.083 --> 21:02.208
[indiscernible conversations]

21:04.333 --> 21:05.417
[man gasping]

21:06.333 --> 21:08.333
‐ Someone tore the faces
off the Yakuza men!

21:09.500 --> 21:11.000
Everybody out!

21:11.000 --> 21:11.958
[people screaming]

21:11.958 --> 21:15.500
‐ What part of sneaking in undetected
do you not understand?

21:16.417 --> 21:19.375
‐ You little punks.
Always stirring shit!

21:19.375 --> 21:22.625
This is war!
‐ Pff. Shut up and die.

21:22.625 --> 21:25.000
[gunfire]

21:25.000 --> 21:26.875
[screeching]

21:35.458 --> 21:37.292
BRYCE: [muffled]
See? See? This is what happens

21:37.292 --> 21:38.917
when you don't stick to the plan!

21:38.917 --> 21:40.833
You gotta listen more, man!
[growls]

21:41.292 --> 21:43.000
Now where you going? Dude!

21:43.000 --> 21:45.708
[hooting]
[men screaming]

21:51.583 --> 21:53.208
[screeching]

21:58.250 --> 21:59.583
‐ We can't stay here.

22:01.583 --> 22:02.917
[grunts]
[clang]

22:02.917 --> 22:04.208
GOON: Goddammit!

22:05.000 --> 22:05.875
AKIKO: Oh, shit.

22:06.708 --> 22:07.583
[grunts]

22:08.375 --> 22:09.375
Wait.

22:09.375 --> 22:10.292
[hoots]

22:10.292 --> 22:12.292
[gunshots]
[man screams]

22:13.667 --> 22:14.792
What the hell?

22:15.667 --> 22:16.667
[gun clatters]

22:21.083 --> 22:22.208
[gasps]

22:23.417 --> 22:26.917
‐ Hey, bud. Sorry to barge in
on your little moment here,

22:26.917 --> 22:28.208
but, uh, the General!

22:28.208 --> 22:30.667
[muffled shouting]

22:30.667 --> 22:33.833
♪

22:35.000 --> 22:38.083
[panting]

22:38.792 --> 22:39.667
[gasps]

22:41.750 --> 22:42.875
‐ Monkey?

22:46.750 --> 22:48.042
[growls]

22:48.042 --> 22:49.750
‐ No! Monkey, no!
[screeches]

22:49.750 --> 22:51.208
[screams]

22:53.625 --> 22:55.250
[screams]

22:55.250 --> 22:57.375
[blood splatters]
[tires squealing]

22:57.375 --> 23:01.500
No! No! Oh, you are the worst, bud!
You know that?

23:01.500 --> 23:04.542
You are literally killing everyone
we're supposed to get info from!

23:04.542 --> 23:07.042
[sighs]
Well, just grab his wallet then.

23:07.042 --> 23:10.125
Grab the wallet please, for the love‐‐
Thank you.

23:10.125 --> 23:12.833
Now how the hell are we supposed
to get out of this shit show?

23:13.417 --> 23:14.583
[gasps]

23:17.417 --> 23:19.583
♪

23:21.250 --> 23:24.000
[sirens wailing]

23:27.333 --> 23:29.792
‐ You know there's going to be
a lot more violence.

23:30.625 --> 23:31.917
Are you ready for it?

23:31.917 --> 23:34.000
‐ Does that mean you're running?
‐ No...

23:34.583 --> 23:36.125
we're running.

23:37.583 --> 23:40.000
‐ Woo‐hoo‐hoo‐hoo‐hoo! Yeah!

23:40.000 --> 23:42.250
Aw, dude, look at you!
"Cape Fear"ing it.

23:42.250 --> 23:43.583
That's so awesome!

23:43.583 --> 23:46.583
Downside is, you're gonna have to pull
a lot of gravel outta your butt‐crack.

23:46.583 --> 23:49.083
[sirens continue]

23:55.375 --> 23:57.458
‐ Guard this house 24 hours a day!

23:57.458 --> 23:59.042
You understand?
‐ Yes, sir!

24:00.500 --> 24:01.625
‐ Oh!

24:03.000 --> 24:05.167
[hoots]
‐ Wow, who is this?

24:05.167 --> 24:07.083
♪

24:10.417 --> 24:12.250
[hoots]

24:12.250 --> 24:14.083
[whimpers]

24:17.042 --> 24:18.542
[chuckles]
It's funny,

24:18.542 --> 24:21.333
I had a crush on my second grade teacher
Mrs. Schwartz.

24:22.250 --> 24:25.083
Then one day I realized
I was in the second grade,

24:25.083 --> 24:27.292
and I literally didn't have
a chance in hell.

24:27.292 --> 24:29.083
[grunts]

24:30.125 --> 24:31.833
Hey, a little sign‐language there.

24:32.583 --> 24:34.375
Looks like we're starting
to make progress, huh?

24:35.375 --> 24:38.583
♪ funky music playing ♪

24:38.583 --> 24:41.875
♪

24:41.875 --> 24:44.917
[distant sirens wailing]

24:45.917 --> 24:47.417
‐ Hmm. Huh.

24:50.875 --> 24:52.125
Hmm.

24:52.125 --> 24:53.542
HARUKA: Ito‐san.
‐ Hmm.

24:53.542 --> 24:55.542
‐ I don't mean to be disrespectful,

24:56.208 --> 24:59.083
but when I came to the city,
I vowed not to change who I am.

24:59.833 --> 25:04.042
I cannot stand by and watch
my partner steal drugs or money or‐‐

25:07.583 --> 25:08.667
‐ Sit.

25:08.667 --> 25:11.708
♪ tense music playing ♪

25:11.708 --> 25:15.792
♪

25:21.542 --> 25:24.792
♪

25:32.792 --> 25:35.542
♪ Kikagaku Moyo's
Dripping Sun playing ♪

25:35.542 --> 25:37.542
♪
